    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.37a.21b"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">21b</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>15 May 1973</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This is in repsonse to your good letter to Blanche Barber. She fell a couple of weeks ago and damaged her back which necessitates her confinement to a convalescent hospital. She is not in great pain, but finds is difficult to move very easily.</p>
                
                <p>She enjoys your letters and has them read again and again.</p>
                
                <p>I am the widow of her nephew, David Ben Everett. As a librarian, I have more than a passing interest in your books and I have deemed it a privilege to know you albeit remotely.</p> 
                
                <p>Write to:
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Blanche Barber</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del/><add>H</add>y Lond Convalescent Hospital</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>3170 <hi rend="caps">M</hi> St.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Merced, Calif. 95340</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Edna Everett</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Edna <hi rend="caps">H.</hi> Everett</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>2377 Shaffer Road</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Atwater, Calif.  95301</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
        </body>
        
